rComments: Great prof and she knows whats up! Meta is hard but she is quite good at explaining the concept! Well done slides very good! Just make sure you study study study and you will do well.

Very unusual. Stars on testable lecture slides (but so many slides with stars that its counter-productive, you just have to learn everything in the end). Not very open to discussing marks. Even less to revising marks.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Tough class and she makes you work for it, but Dr. Aguer was kind enough to let us know which slides would be tested on, and she devised a summary sheet of all the reactions for us. She isn't my favourite lecturer but she isn't bad by any means.

Very knowledgeable prof, puts stars on the slides that are testable (i.e. on exam) so you are not wasting your time studying the wrong things. Evaluations are all very fair and exactly what she would have you expect, though metabolism is and will always be a difficult subject. Focuses on importance of regulating steps in evaluation. Would recommend

The class is very focused on memorization but Celine tries her best to make it easier. The quizzes are an easy way to boost marks and she is very specific on which parts of her lectures she will test you on. The midterms are very fair as long as you study and she gives great feedback on them although she is slow to evaluate them.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: The class is very well organized. The notes are clear and she indicates exactly which slides will be on the midterms and exam. Quizzes are a great way to make sure you are always reviewing the material. Lots of memorization is required but she tells you exactly what she expects as an answer for each question on her midterm and exam.

She is very clear, her exam questions are not particularly hard. Her quizzes are fairly easy when you review your notes a little. You can easily ace this course if you a VERY good at memorizing details. She tells you exactly what slides that will be evaluated, however you must remember every detail & when answering the questions be beyond specific.
